<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Suffolk" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Suffolk,</orth> name of an English county: <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.156" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.8.12" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 8, 12</bibl>. <emph>Earl</emph> or <emph>Duke of S.</emph> the baronial title of several peers famous in English history: <bibl n="shak. h5 4.6.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 6, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.6.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 6, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.6.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 6, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.6.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 6, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.8.108" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 8, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 53</bibl>. 132 etc. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 17</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 17</bibl> 124 etc. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 1, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 1, 17</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 8</bibl>.
